GenericContext
public static enum GenericContext.ConcurrencyModel
extends java.lang.Enum<GenericContext.ConcurrencyModel>

Our three different models for concurrency. SYNCHRONIZED means use a synchronized map (appropriate for request or session scoped components that see little contention). CONCURRENT means use a ConcurrentHashMap (appropriate for globally accessible Contexts that change often), DISPOSABLE means use a disposable, unsynchronized HashMap (appropriate for globally accessible Contexts that change rarely).
